    "reasoning": "The module stimulus_gen needs to generate control signals for the testbench. All outputs are logic type. The wavedrom signals are registered but not reset, so initialize them with initial blocks. The clk is used for generating the signals. The predict_valid and train_mispredicted are pulses triggered periodically. Use localparams for states. Avoid using 'inside' operator by using == for state checks. Use always @* for combinational logic. All sequential blocks use posedge clk. Initialize registers with non-blocking assignments. Ensure outputs are driven in all branches. Signals like areset should be controlled with counters. Timeout handling with a timer. For the wavedrom queues, track errors with flags and use non-blocking assignments.",
    "module": "module stimulus_gen (input clk, output logic areset, output logic predict_valid, output logic predict_taken, output logic train_mispredicted, output logic train_taken, output logic [31:0] train_history, input tb_match, output reg [511:0] wavedrom_title, output reg wavedrom_enable, output reg wavedrom_hide_after_time);\n\n// State variables for training and prediction phases\nlocalparam TRAIN = 0, PREDICT = 1;\nreg state;\n\n// Timer for timeouts\nreg [31:0] timer;\n\n// Error tracking\nreg error_detected;\n\n// Train history shift register\nreg [31:0] history_reg;\n\ninitial begin\n    areset = 1;\n    predict_valid = 0;\n    train_mispredicted = 0;\n    predict_taken = 0;\n    train_taken = 0;\n    history_reg = 0;\n    state = TRAIN;\n    timer = 0;\n    error_detected = 0;\n    wavedrom_title = 0;\n    wavedrom_enable = 0;\n    wavedrom_hide_after_time = 0;\nend\n\n// Asynchronous areset generation\nalways @(posedge clk) begin\n    if (timer >= 1000) begin\n        areset <= 0;\n        timer <= 0;\n    end else begin\n        timer <= timer + 1;\n    end\nend\n\n// State machine for training and predicting\nalways @(posedge clk) begin\n    if (areset) begin\n        state <= TRAIN;\n        timer <= 0;\n    end else begin\n        timer <= timer + 1;\n        case (state)\n            TRAIN: begin\n                if (timer % 50 == 0) begin\n                    state <= PREDICT;\n                end\n            end\n            PREDICT: begin\n                if (timer % 100 == 0) begin\n                    state <= TRAIN;\n                end\n                if (timer % 10 == 0 && !error_detected) begin\n                    predict_valid <= 1;\n                    predict_taken <= (timer % 2 == 0);\n                end\n            end\n        endcase\n    end\nend\n\n// Train misprediction handling\nalways @(posedge clk) begin\n    if (train_mispredicted) begin\n        history_reg <= {history_reg[30:0], train_taken};\n    end else if (predict_valid && tb_match && !train_mispredicted) begin\n        history_reg <= {history_reg[30:0], predict_taken};\n    end\nend\n\n// Generate train_history from history_reg\nassign train_history = history_reg;\n\n// Timeout for errors\nalways @(posedge clk) begin\n    if (timer >= 10000 && !error_detected) begin\n        error_detected <= 1;\n        wavedrom_title <= \"Timeout\";\n        wavedrom_enable <= 1;\n        wavedrom_hide_after_time <= 5000;\n    end\nend\n\n// Wavedrom signals driven by state\nalways @(posedge clk) begin\n    if (state == PREDICT && predict_valid) begin\n        wavedrom_enable <= 1;\n    end else if (error_detected) begin\n        wavedrom_enable <= 0;\n    end\nend\n\n// Continuous assignments for non-sequential logic\nassign predict_taken = state == PREDICT && (timer % 2 == 0);\n\nendmodule\n\nmodule tb();\n    reg clk;\n    reg tb_match;\n    wire [31:0] train_history;\n    wire [31:0] predict_history;\n    // Instantiate DUT and RefModule\n    // ... ommitted for brevity\nendmodule"
